    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Heap structure that allows fast access and updates.</para>
<para>Templated on the comparator HC_ so that the same data structure can service both distance-style searches (HC_ = CMax&lt;float, int32_t&gt;, smaller is better) and similarity-style searches (HC_ = CMin&lt;float, int32_t&gt;, larger is better). For the distance variant the underlying heap is a max-heap and &quot;pop_min&quot; returns the closest element; for similarity the underlying heap is a min-heap and &quot;pop_min&quot; returns the most similar element. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
